        // The smallest value it can take is a[i].
        // The largest value it can take is (a[i] + x) % m.
        // If a[i] >= prev_val, we can just keep it as a[i] (by not incrementing it enough times
        // to make it wrap around and become smaller than prev_val, or by incrementing it
        // such that it stays >= prev_val).
