        // 1. k <= c (we need at least k coders)
        // 2. k <= m (we need at least k mathematicians)
        // 3. 3k <= c + m + x (total students available)
        // From 1 and 2, k <= min(c, m).
        // From 3, k <= (c + m + x) / 3.
