        // Since `s` is a palindrome, `s[n-1] = s[n-2] = ... = s[n - (n/2)] = c`.
        // So `s` is of the form `c...c [middle_part] c...c`.
        // The `middle_part` is either empty (if `n` is even) or `s[n/2]` (if `n` is odd).
        // If `n` is even, `s = c...c c...c`. All characters are `c`.
        // If `n` is odd, `s = c...c d c...c`.
        //
        // So, the condition "all characters in `s.substr(0, n/2)` are the same"
        // implies that `s` is either `c...c` (all same characters) or `c...c d c...c`.
        //
        // If `s` is `c...c` (all same characters), it's impossible.
        // If `s` is `c...c d c...c` (e.g., "aba", "level", "madam"), where `c` is the character
